    <description>
      Dynamic data is Rx for Collections. It provides an observable list and an observable cache both having at least 50 collection specific operators. These operators enable filtering, sorting, grouping, transforms, binding, pagination, virtualisation, expiration, disposal management plus more.
      They are implemented as extensions which allow simple semantics to define powerful and declarative data transformations. The magic is that when the source observable collection is modified, the operators self-maintain. The result is very difficult data management can be reduced to a few lines of code.
    </description>
